### Payment API tests (backend)
### Use with VS Code "REST Client" extension, or copy curl commands to terminal.
### Base URL (default): http://localhost:3000/api

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@email = your-email@example.com
@password = your-password

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 1) Login – get JWT (replace @email and @password above or in request body)
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 2) Create checkout (card-only) – requires JWT from step 1
### Replace the Authorization Bearer token with the access_token from login response.
### Replace course id/name/price with real course data from your DB if needed.
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# @name createCheckoutCards
POST {{baseUrl}}/payments/create-checkout-cards
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.access_token}}

{
  "items": [
    {
      "id": "course-id-from-database",
      "name": "Test Course",
      "price": 9.99,
      "quantity": 1
    }
  ],
  "successUrl": "http://localhost:3030/product/checkout/success",
  "cancelUrl": "http://localhost:3030/product/checkout",
  "currency": "USD"
}

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 2b) Multiple products (cart) – same endpoint, multiple items in "items" array
### Use real course IDs from your DB (each id = one course; used for enrollment after payment).
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# @name createCheckoutCardsMultiple
POST {{baseUrl}}/payments/create-checkout-cards
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.access_token}}

{
  "items": [
    {
      "id": "course-id-1",
      "name": "AI Community Building Fundamentals",
      "price": 49,
      "quantity": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "course-id-2",
      "name": "Advanced Workflow Automation",
      "price": 89,
      "quantity": 1
    }
  ],
  "successUrl": "https://www.google.com/",
  "cancelUrl": "https://www.google.com/",
  "currency": "USD"
}

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 3) Create checkout (default payment methods) – same as above, different endpoint
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# @name createCheckout
POST {{baseUrl}}/payments/create-checkout
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.access_token}}

{
  "items": [
    {
      "id": "course-id-from-database",
      "name": "Test Course",
      "price": 9.99,
      "quantity": 1
    }
  ],
  "successUrl": "http://localhost:3030/product/checkout/success",
  "cancelUrl": "http://localhost:3030/product/checkout",
  "currency": "USD"
}

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 4) Without auth – should return 401
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/payments/create-checkout-cards
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "items": [{ "id": "c1", "name": "Course", "price": 10, "quantity": 1 }],
  "successUrl": "https://example.com/success",
  "cancelUrl": "https://example.com/cancel"
}

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 5) Empty cart – should return 400 "Cart is empty"
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/payments/create-checkout-cards
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.access_token}}

{
  "items": [],
  "successUrl": "https://example.com/success",
  "cancelUrl": "https://example.com/cancel"
}

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 6) Webhook (for reference – usually called by WooshPay, not manually)
### Without valid Signature header you may get 401 if PAYMENT_WEBHOOK_SECRET is set.
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/payments/webhook
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "payment_intent.succeeded",
  "data": {
    "object": {
      "client_reference_id": "user-id|course-id-1,course-id-2",
      "payment_status": "paid"
    }
  }
}
